These projects are large-scale reconfigurable robots - 8-foot-long and 12-foot-long proteins.
They are embedded in electromechanical devices, sensors.
You need to decode the way you want to fold into a series of angles - negative 120 degrees, negative 120 degrees, 0 degrees, 0 degrees, 120 degrees, negative 120 degrees, and so on; a series of angles, or turns, can be transmitted by wire.
